#. <section class="sutta" id="sn36.20"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn36.20:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 36"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 36"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.20:0.2"
msgid "2. Rahogatavagga"
msgstr "2. In Private"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn36.20:0.3"
msgid "20. Bhikkhusutta"
msgstr "20. A Mendicant"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.229"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.20:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Dvepi mayā, bhikkhave, vedanā vuttā pariyāyena, tissopi mayā vedanā vuttā "
"pariyāyena, pañcapi mayā vedanā vuttā pariyāyena, chapi mayā vedanā vuttā "
"pariyāyena, aṭṭhārasāpi mayā vedanā vuttā pariyāyena, chattiṃsāpi mayā "
"vedanā vuttā pariyāyena, aṭṭhasatampi mayā vedanā vuttā pariyāyena."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, in one explanation I’ve spoken of two feelings. In another "
"explanation I’ve spoken of three feelings, or five, six, eighteen, thirty-"
"six, or a hundred and eight feelings."

msgctxt "sn36.20:1.2"
msgid "Evaṃ pariyāyadesito, bhikkhave, mayā dhammo."
msgstr "I’ve taught the Dhamma with all these explanations."

msgctxt "sn36.20:1.3"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ pariyāyadesite kho, bhikkhave, mayā dhamme ye aññamaññassa subhāsitaṃ "
"sulapitaṃ na samanumaññissanti, na samanujānissanti, na samanumodissanti, "
"tesaṃ etaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—bhaṇḍanajātā kalahajātā vivādāpannā aññamaññaṃ "
"mukhasattīhi vitudantā viharissantīti."
msgstr ""
"This being so, you can expect that those who don’t concede, approve, or "
"agree with what has been well spoken will argue, quarrel, and fight, "
"continually wounding each other with barbed words."

msgctxt "sn36.20:1.4"
msgid "Evaṃ pariyāyadesito, bhikkhave, mayā dhammo."
msgstr "I’ve taught the Dhamma with all these explanations."

msgctxt "sn36.20:1.5"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ pariyāyadesite kho, bhikkhave, mayā dhamme ye aññamaññassa subhāsitaṃ "
"sulapitaṃ samanumaññissanti samanujānissanti samanumodissanti, tesaṃ etaṃ "
"pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā khīrodakībhūtā aññamaññaṃ "
"piyacakkhūhi sampassantā viharissantīti."
msgstr ""
"This being so, you can expect that those who do concede, approve, or agree "
"with what has been well spoken will live in harmony, appreciating each "
"other, without quarreling, blending like milk and water, and regarding each "
"other with kindly eyes."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.20:2.1"
msgid "Pañcime, bhikkhave, kāmaguṇā … pe …"
msgstr "There are these five kinds of sensual stimulation. …"

msgctxt "sn36.20:2.2"
msgid ""
"ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, bhikkhave, vijjati yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ "
"vadeyyuṃ:"
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say:"

msgctxt "sn36.20:2.3"
msgid "‘saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samaṇo gotamo āha, tañca sukhasmiṃ paññapeti."
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama spoke of the cessation of perception and feeling, and he "
"includes it in happiness."

msgctxt "sn36.20:2.4"
msgid "Tayidaṃ kiṃsu, tayidaṃ kathaṃsū’ti?"
msgstr "What’s up with that?’"

msgctxt "sn36.20:2.5"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā:"
msgstr ""
"Mendicants, when wanderers who follow other paths say this, you should say "
"to them:"

msgctxt "sn36.20:2.6"
msgid ""
"‘na kho, āvuso, bhagavā sukhaññeva vedanaṃ sandhāya sukhasmiṃ paññapeti."
msgstr ""
"‘Reverends, when the Buddha describes what’s included in happiness, he’s not "
"just referring to pleasant feeling."

#. VAR: yahiṃ yahiṃ → yaṃ hi yaṃ hi (bj) | yamhi yamhi (pts1)
msgctxt "sn36.20:2.7"
msgid ""
"Yattha yattha, āvuso, sukhaṃ upalabbhati yahiṃ yahiṃ, taṃ taṃ tathāgato "
"sukhasmiṃ paññapetī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"The Realized One describes pleasure as included in happiness wherever it’s "
"found, and in whatever context.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.20:2.8"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.20:2.9"
msgid "Rahogatavaggo dutiyo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.20:3.1"
msgid "Rahogataṃ dve ākāsaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.20:3.2"
msgid "agāraṃ dve ca ānandā;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.20:3.3"
msgid "Sambahulā duve vuttā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.20:3.4"
msgid "pañcakaṅgo ca bhikkhunāti."
msgstr ""
